## Using the Space 

All of your Online professional learning will be done here, in Code Studio. Below you'll find a quick tour of the interface, which demonstrates several important features of using Code Studio:
<br>


The main PD page is broken up into several __stages__, which each represent a different topic or idea

<h4><details>
<summary>click here to see more about stages</summary>
<br>
<div><em>once you're finished viewing this, click the arrow above to collapse the section</em></div>
<br>
<img src ="/script_assets/pd/pd_stage_overview.gif" />
</details></h4>

<br>

Each stage is made up of __levels__, which hold individual videos, readings, or questions. 

Some levels are indicated by the circles with numbers, and are visible on the main page header in any level, and also from the header drop-down in any level.

The colors of level circles will change based on your progress. In this program you'll see the following types of circles:

![/script_assets/pd/stage_states.png](/script_assets/pd/stage_states.png)
<br/><br/>

For video or reading levels, the icons will go grey when completed.
